page.title: 01Geography of Winmarleigh
page.content: Physically the area is divided into 2 distinct parts,the western half of reclaimed (with a remnant of 'wild') {mossland,}and, the eastern half of{ {clays,sands and gravels}of glacial deposition.The mossland is of some {8m.O.D.}and is separated from the land of the east by the{Hillhouse Coast,} now greatly eroded,of the immediate post-glacial period.This land rises from about{15m. to 30m.O.D.} The settlement is almost totally dispersed,the older mossland farms being located on esker-like and drumlinoid features which rise above the level of the{bog.}The apparent nucleation of Winmarleigh is totally modern and represents the sum of recent development. The township of Winmarleigh occupies some 60% of the study area with the north west 40% part of Cockerham.
